                  "step": "Add numerators",
                  "explanation": "Keep common denominator",
                  "calculation": "$\\frac{3 + 2}{x} = \\frac{5}{x}$"
                },
                {
                  "step": "State restrictions",
                  "explanation": "Original denominator: $x \\neq 0$",
                  "calculation": "$x \\neq 0$"
                }
              ],
              
              "final_answer": "$\\frac{5}{x}$, where $x \\neq 0$",
              "concept_applied": "When denominators are the same, add numerators and keep the denominator."
